<br>
Its not hopeless.  You can often get the advantage over your opponent.  The problem is that when you do...almost anyone can escape from you easy enough right before you get the kill and you have no means of stopping them.  BTW, its not wizards and druids and necros snare/root/darkness that allows them to get the kill before their opponent escapes.  Those spells are universally resisted.  Its the fact that they all have effective DD spells that cast faster than gate.  We have scars of course...but it just doesn't seem to be that effective.  I think it is too easily resisted.  Char is basically my bread and butter PvP spell.  It is harder to resist than scars.  When I cast it on myself with 150fr it still seems to do quite a bit of damage most of the time.  But that 4.5s cast time makes it hard to win any nuke trading contest with it.  One secret though is to add scintillation to your spell line-up.  Its also hard to resist like charr but has only a 3s cast time.  (long recast though unfortunately)  <br>
<br>
Foryst<br>
Level 54 Mage SZ <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/upellaeonragnarok.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Pellaeon Ragnarok</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#333333>(2/26/02 1:14:38 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=44.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_cry.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: mages a good choice for Sullen zek?</span><hr size=1> I will have to agree with the above posters who play in Sullon Zek.  I play a mage in SZ (lvl 55), and I can tell you we are the worst PvP class by far <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I started a mage because I *thought* their nukes + pet would make a great offense, but after level 40 this wasn't the case at all.  Here's why:<br>
<br>
#1. Your pets are easily taken out of the equation<br>
<br>
Almost any class that can cast spells will easily eiliminate your pet.  Root/snare/fear/mez/charm/blind...you name it.  Bards and enchanters can also instantly kill your pets by casting charm.  There goes your #1 weapon... you are now a second-rate Wizard without crowd control <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br>
<br>
#2.  No crowd control  <br>
<br>
You have no way of fighting vs more than 2 players.  You can't root/snare/mez/charm etc, so everyone can simply run up to you, or run away from you if you happen to be winning a fight.  Pet root and other spells will mostly land on players who con green to you.<br>
<br>
There is a bug with the Annul magic series of spells which kills our pets if we cast it on a player, so you can forget about casting it for PvP (I think it's bugged in PvE as well).  The malise series, even though it has 1.5x more debuff value in SZ, will almost never land on an even or red con opponent.<br>
<br>
#3. You are dead at the 50+ PvP game<br>
<br>
Pre-50, you can hold your own basically because others will lack resist gear.  But in the high-end PvP, you'll be the easiest target around.  Tanks will demolish you in seconds, casters will outnuke you, and hybrids will do a combination of both.  <br>
<br>
#4 Caster/pet classes nerfs<br>
<br>
Casters can only do 66% damage on nukes.  So if your char does 690 damage max against monsters, you'll only be able to do about 480dmg *max* against a player.  At level 50+ you won't get many max damage hits since everyone runs around in full BD resist gear.<br>
<br>
Pets are also nerfed.  They do around 50% damage or less in PvP.  You won't see Jabober hitting for 58 damage like he does against mobs, he'll be hitting for 30ish or so max against players.<br>
<br>
As you can see, mages are the casters that are affected the most by these damage nerfs since we rely greatly on our pets.<br>
----------------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
Because of all this, I stopped leveling up my Magician and started a tank to play in SZ.  Tanks can hit for 100% damage contrary to casters, and with BD resist gear they are very hard to take down in PvP (unless you are a wizard with manaburn).  Don't play a mage in Sullon unless you have no other choice whatsoever.<br>
<br>
